Description. Adult.
Colouration. Body yellow to ochreous dorsally and ventrally, dark brown to almost black laterally (
Fig. 71
). Head yellowish with brown longitudinal band in the middle of vertex and on genal processes (
Fig. 73
). Eyes greyish or reddish, ocelli yellow or orange. Antennal segments 1, 2 yellowish or light brown; segment 3–7 yellow in basal part, dark brown in apical part, darker portion increasing towards apical segments; segments 8–10 almost black. Clypeus yellow; rostrum yellow with black tip. Pronotum dirty yellowish. Mesopraescutum and mesoscutum with two and four longitudinal brown stripes, respectively. Legs brown; tibiae and tarsi yellow. Forewing transparent, membrane ochreous to light brown, veins yellow to brown, apex of clavus dark brown (
Fig. 75
). Hindwing transparent, whitish to yellowish. Abdominal sclerites dark brown. Male proctiger and parameres light brown, subgenital plate dark brown, tip of parameres black; female terminalia irregularly lighter and darker brown. Light colour in younger specimens more expanded.

Structure. Body 1.6–1.8 times as long as wide. Antenna 7-segmented, 2.6–3.1 times as long as forewing pad which has 10–12 or more medium long or long setae dorsally and 15–17 weakly capitate marginal setae. Circumanal ring (
Fig. 103
) small, distance from anus to outer circumanal ring about as long as that from there to group of sectasetae, rounded laterally; consisting of several rows of pores except medially.

Measurements (in mm) and ratios (
4 immatures
). Body length 2.28–2.32, antenna length 1.72–1.84.
